ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W4_CampusMaintenanceRequestApp

Class Name: CampusMaintenanceRequestApp

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 70–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 76 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a campus maintenance request system that validates requests, assigns valid requests
to available maintenance teams, and prints assignment reports.

Program Flow
The main method creates a MaintenanceCenter, registers several MaintenanceTeam objects,
reports several MaintenanceRequest objects, assigns requests, and prints the result.

Class Responsibilities
CampusMaintenanceRequestApp starts the program.
MaintenanceCenter coordinates registration, validation, assignment, and reports.
MaintenanceRequest stores request data.
MaintenanceTeam defines common team state and behavior.
Concrete team classes decide which request type they can handle.

Object Collaboration
Main creates teams and requests.
Main passes them to MaintenanceCenter.
MaintenanceCenter asks each team whether it can handle each request.
Concrete teams answer through overridden canHandle() methods.
MaintenanceCenter stores assignment results.

Requirements
Use polymorphism for assignment logic.
Do not use instanceof for team capability checks.
Validate requests before storing them.
Use ArrayList and HashMap.
Handle invalid requests without stopping the program.